'''Art Jericho''' is a [[contemporary art]] gallery in [[Jericho, Oxford|Jericho]], northwest central [[Oxford]], [[England]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.dailyinfo.co.uk/reviews/venue/1458/Art_Jericho | title=Art Jericho | publisher=[[Daily Information]] | location=UK | accessdate=22 April 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.artrabbit.com/organisations/art-jericho | title=Gallery: Art Jericho | publisher=Art Rabbit | accessdate=22 April 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.list.co.uk/place/20002360-art-jericho/ | title=Art Jericho | publisher=[[The List (magazine)|The List]] | location=UK | accessdate=22 April 2016 }}</ref>
The gallery is managed by Jenny Blyth Fine Art.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.jennyblythfineart.co.uk/ | title=Jenny Blyth Fine Art | location=UK | accessdate=22 April 2016 }}</ref> It participates in the annual [[Oxfordshire Artweeks]] art festival each May<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.artweeks.org/festival/2016/andrew-walton-art-jericho | title=Andrew Walton At Art Jericho | website=[[Oxfordshire Artweeks]] | accessdate=22 April 2016 }}</ref> and holds regular temporary exhibitions for artists.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://theoxfordculturereview.com/tag/art-jericho/ | title=Posts Tagged ‘Art Jericho’ – Ground Work: An Interview with Andrew Walton & David Attwooll | work=[[The Oxford Culture Review]] | date=21 April 2014 | accessdate=22 April 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/14306001.Beauty_is_preserved_in_glass_works_for_new_exhibition/ | title=Oxfordshire scenery captured in glass for new Art Jericho exhibition by Kingham artist Helen Slater | newspaper=[[Oxford Mail]] | date=26 February 2016 | first=Kieran | last=Davey | accessdate=22 April 2016 }}</ref> Concerts are sometimes held at the gallery.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.songkick.com/venues/1332476-art-jericho-gallery | title=Art Jericho Gallery – Oxford | website=SongKick | accessdate=22 April 2016 }}</ref>
